d No.\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"1 Andy Murray was bragging that he had scored a rare one from Guam, the island in the Western Pacific that has just eight athletes in Paris.\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1684, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1546, \"end\": 1557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.050734727406477e-32, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 1606, \"end\": 1610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guam_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9195351716221993, \"rank\": 0.08750598132160643, \"text\": \"Guam\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guam_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guam_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1678, \"end\": 1683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.99999999970305, \"rank\": 2.970284918043293e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The official Olympics website traces pin trading back to the first modern Games in 1896, where athletes wore cardboard badges.\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1812, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost 130 years on, the range on offer has exploded with everyone from national organizing committees and sporting federations to media companies and sponsors offering their enameled mementos.\", \"from\": 1814, \"to\": 2007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Retired tennis star Serena Williams - a self-proclaimed \\\"first-class pin collector\\\" - says she started amassing them at the 2000 Sydney Olympics.\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2154, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2029, \"end\"